$$
\text{HardShrink}(x) = \begin{cases}
    x & |x| > \lambda \\
    0 & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
$$

Discontinuous at $x = \pm\lambda$ — for an everywhere-continuous
alternative use `softshrink` (the proximal operator of the
$\ell_1$ norm).

$$
\text{threshold}(x; t, v) = \begin{cases}
    x & x > t \\
    v & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
$$

Discontinuous at $x = t$ when $v \ne t$; the derivative
is $1$ above the threshold and $0$ below.  Useful as a
deterministic alternative to `relu` when a non-zero "off"
value is needed (e.g. setting masked positions to a sentinel).

